<TITLE> Some govt posts shuffled </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com)Wing commander Tomid Aziz Khan, general manager (security) of Bangladesh Biman, has been brought back to his previous workplace, the establishment ministry said in a circular Wednesday. Meanwhile, the government has halted until Nov 22 the transfer of Mahmudul Karim, economic minister (joint secretary) of the Bangladesh Permanent Mission to the United Nations, to the establishment ministry as OSD. The OSD order was issued on Feb 11. Some other administrative changes have also been made: Bazlur Rahman, deputy secretary of the textiles and jute ministry, has been transferred to the Energy Regulatory Commission as project director. Mir Mohammad Aslam Uddin, assistant press secretary to the president, has been placed with the information ministry. Major Nurul Amin and Major Anisur Rahman have been deputed to the Survey of Bangladesh as assistant survey officers. bdnew
